The paper deals with the approximability of a computational problem, which suggests that it could belong to the category of Computational Complexity (cs.CC). The problem involves constraints on sets of variables, which could also fall under the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The use of algebraic combinatorial properties and the study of hard Max CSP problems suggest that the paper could also belong to the categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM).
